# Project Protection (UI-only work)

This is a production app. Current work is **UI/UX improvement only**. Prefer not changing anything until the architecture is understood; when editing, protect behavior below.

## Never change

- Backend logic, database queries, entities, schemas, API calls
- Authentication, permissions, calculations, validations, data-processing
- Existing feature behavior or workflows
- Field names, routes, functions, props, env vars, or integrations (no remove/rename)
- Real data — do not replace with mock/fake data
- Working code unless required for UI presentation
- Loading, error, success, and empty-state **logic** (visual restyle is OK)

## Do not

- Install unnecessary dependencies
- Rewrite large parts of the app — small, incremental edits only
- Modify code when uncertain whether it is business logic — leave it alone

## Allowed

- Layout, typography, colors, spacing, responsive behavior
- Accessibility, visual hierarchy, styling, animations
- Reusable **presentational** components
- User-facing microcopy **without changing meaning**
- Reorganizing UI components **if** inputs, outputs, and functionality stay the same

## Before editing a file

1. Identify logic that must be preserved (handlers, queries, auth, validation, state machines, side effects).
2. Touch only presentation: classNames, structure wrappers, tokens, a11y attributes, copy phrasing.
3. Keep props, callbacks, data shapes, and control flow intact.

## After every change

- Run the build and fix **only** issues caused by the UI work.
- Do not “clean up” unrelated logic, APIs, or entities while fixing build errors.
